==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embiotocoid
<hw>Em`bi*ot"o*coid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>Embiotoca</ets>, the name of one genus + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>Belonging to, or resembling, the
<fam>Embiotocid⟦ae⟧</fam>.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>One of a
family of fishes (<fam>Embiotocid⟦ae⟧</fam>) abundant on the coast of
California, remarkable for being viviparous; -- also called
<altname>surf fish</altname> and <altname>viviparous fish</altname>. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> in Appendix.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

